			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/7912d7cb34388f320be87f070b324ee7?s=40&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/7912d7cb34388f320be87f070b324ee7?s=80&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' />				<cite class="fn">Nana</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>			</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
				
			<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="index.html#comment-545000">
				December 28, 2018 at 16:19					</a>
									</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

				<div class="comment-body"><p>The recent episode of Black Mirror, &#8220;Bandersnatch,&#8221; is an interactive piece. It runs 90 minutes on its default path, but also has multiple other scenes you can branch off to, albeit ones which would cause a gameplay with less time. Would Bandersnatch qualify for Long Form or Short Form?</p>
</div>

				<div class="reply">
				<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?replytocom=545000#respond' data-commentid="545000" data-postid="11" data-belowelement="comment-545000" data-respondelement="respond" aria-label='Reply to Nana'>Reply</a>				</div><!-- .reply -->
